## Documentation Tools and Technologies

### Recommended Markdown Tools

- **Markdown Editors**: VS Code with Markdown Preview, Obsidian
- **Link Checking**: markdown-link-check, Lychee
- **Formatting**: Prettier, markdownlint
- **Generation**: GitBook, MkDocs, Docusaurus, Hugo

### Documentation Hosting

- **GitHub Pages**: Ideal for projects living in GitHub; deploy with GitHub Actions
- **Static Site Generators**: MkDocs, Docusaurus, Hugo for more customization
- **Docs Platforms**: ReadTheDocs, GitBook for professional documentation
- **Wikis**: GitHub Wikis for collaborative documentation (link from README)

### AI-Assisted Documentation

- Use GitHub Copilot for documentation suggestions and code examples
- Leverage AI tools to generate initial documentation structure
- Always review AI-generated content for accuracy and compliance with this ruleset
- Use AI to identify gaps and undocumented code sections
- Maintain human review and final approval of all AI-assisted documentation

