## Enforcement and Quality Metrics

### Linting and Formatting

- Use markdownlint to enforce markdown style consistency
- Use Prettier for automatic formatting (if applicable)
- Integrate linting into pre-commit hooks and CI/CD pipelines
- Maintain a `.markdownlintrc` file with project-specific rules

### Documentation Quality Checklist

Before merging documentation:

- [ ] Follows Diátaxis category (Tutorial/How-To/Reference/Explanation)
- [ ] Purpose is clear in the first paragraph
- [ ] Uses plain language appropriate for target audience
- [ ] Contains at least one concrete example
- [ ] Links are working and point to current information
- [ ] Follows consistent formatting and style
- [ ] Includes a table of contents if longer than 5 sections
- [ ] Code examples are complete and executable
- [ ] Related documentation is cross-linked
- [ ] No outdated or broken references
- [ ] Matches tone and voice of existing documentation

