## Documentation as Code (Docs as Code) Practice

### Principles

- Treat documentation like source code
- Version control all documentation
- Review documentation changes in PRs like code changes
- Test documentation (broken links, outdated examples)
- Automate documentation generation where possible
- Use plain text formats (Markdown, AsciiDoc) not proprietary formats
- Keep documentation in the same repository as code when practical

### Workflow

1. Create a documentation-related branch for changes
2. Make documentation changes in markdown files
3. Submit PR for review with documentation-specific checklist
4. Receive feedback from documentation and domain experts
5. Iterate on feedback
6. Merge when approved
7. Documentation builds and deploys automatically via CI/CD

