## Final Notes

This ruleset should be adapted to your project's specific needs. Tailor it by:

- Adding project-specific sections or examples
- Adjusting terminology to match your project's domain
- Extending with language-specific documentation conventions
- Creating templates for common documentation types
- Building custom CI/CD checks for your documentation

Documentation is an ongoing commitment. Treat it with the same rigor and care as your codebase. Good documentation reduces support burden, increases adoption, improves collaboration, and honors your users' time and intelligence.
